00:24:20.252 --> 00:24:24.242
understand. And that was the beginning of the Cancer Dependency Map, and I

406
00:24:24.272 --> 00:24:28.012
jumped in at that point in time thinking that this could be really

407
00:24:28.072 --> 00:24:31.682
powerful. And so the Cancer Dependency Map, and now what we've

408
00:24:31.732 --> 00:24:35.592
launched called PDEP, which is a subset of this but is focused on pediatric

409
00:24:35.632 --> 00:24:39.602
cancer. There's now over 1,000 cell lines, many different

410
00:24:39.652 --> 00:24:42.832
types of cancer, all of which have been sequenced DNA, RNA

411
00:24:42.872 --> 00:24:46.052
methylation. Then you do CRISPR screening.

412
00:24:46.092 --> 00:24:48.652
Initially sh, now it's CRISPR screening.

413
00:24:48.692 --> 00:24:52.484
Turn off every gene one by one.And you can say all the RAS mutant

