00:34:18.935 --> 00:34:22.574
Sciences and decides to come back to the lab.

575
00:34:22.654 --> 00:34:26.364
So we're looking at what else is in these dependencies.

576
00:34:26.915 --> 00:34:30.834
And Hayden gets intrigued by this dependency here that we

577
00:34:30.894 --> 00:34:31.794
call FIP.

578
00:34:32.955 --> 00:34:36.794
And so what she finds is, here's the rest of the cell lines in

579
00:34:36.834 --> 00:34:39.554
DepMap, the now over 1,000 other cell lines.

580
00:34:39.614 --> 00:34:42.574
Here's rhabdoid tumors that are SMARCB1 deficient.

581
00:34:42.634 --> 00:34:46.154
And here's a version of ovarian cancer called small cell carcinoma of the

582
00:34:46.294 --> 00:34:49.594
ovary that's got mutations in the SMARCA4 subunit of

583
00:34:49.694 --> 00:34:50.294
SwitchNif.

584
00:34:51.834 --> 00:34:55.303
And so FIP, it has chromatin binding domains,

585
00:34:55.435 --> 00:34:59.254
bromodomains, Tudor domains, and it's overexpressed in several cancer

