00:35:37.274 --> 00:35:40.994
ligase complex. And when she knocks down FIP in the

598
00:35:41.034 --> 00:35:44.924
chromatin fraction, the members of that E3 complex no

599
00:35:45.054 --> 00:35:48.864
longer bind to DNA. This was a bit surprising because

600
00:35:48.864 --> 00:35:52.394
this complex can interact with multiple different E3 adapter

601
00:35:52.434 --> 00:35:56.324
proteins, and yet getting rid of FIP is enough to get it to go away,

602
00:35:56.474 --> 00:36:00.134
shown here with an siRNA knockdown of FIP,

603
00:36:00.394 --> 00:36:02.914
what happens to the DDB1 subunit.

604
00:36:04.254 --> 00:36:08.074
And so now again, we're really getting deep into transcriptional regulation is

605
00:36:08.094 --> 00:36:10.474
what's going on here and becoming vulnerabilities.

