617
00:36:49.374 --> 00:36:52.694
And if you look at Nurd bound sites where there's no FIP, no change.

618
00:36:53.424 --> 00:36:55.754
And so reading this out, FIP is normally here.

619
00:36:56.014 --> 00:36:59.594
It's recruiting the CRL4 subunit here.

620
00:37:00.074 --> 00:37:04.073
When you knock down FIP, the E3 complex is no longer recruited.

621
00:37:05.154 --> 00:37:08.374
Nurd, one of the things it does is a histone deacetylase.

622
00:37:09.554 --> 00:37:13.054
And so when you now see increased levels of CHD4,

623
00:37:13.454 --> 00:37:16.754
you're now seeing decreased levels of H4

624
00:37:16.794 --> 00:37:20.618
acetylation.Why is this coming up

625
00:37:20.758 --> 00:37:23.478
specifically in SwitchNIF mutant cancers?

626
00:37:23.507 --> 00:37:27.488
And so when she looked at a mutation here that

627
00:37:27.558 --> 00:37:31.458
inactivates both subunits, ATPase subunits of SwitchNIF, it

628
00:37:31.558 --> 00:37:35.398
creates a strong dependency compared to just losing one or the other.

629
00:37:36.498 --> 00:37:40.108
Because of our earlier finding of publishing synthetic lethality between the two

