00:38:22.618 --> 00:38:26.538
effect, but that is because this was a pooled assay, and so

643
00:38:26.598 --> 00:38:29.888
what's coming out the other end are cells that have now regained

644
00:38:29.938 --> 00:38:33.798
expression of FIP. So when we're growing cells in

645
00:38:33.838 --> 00:38:35.028
culture, we don't

646
00:38:35.118 --> 00:38:38.588
overcome that

647
00:38:38.598 --> 00:38:42.378
dependence. And so normally, SwitchNIF is antagonizing the NRD

648
00:38:42.438 --> 00:38:44.468
complex at enhancers and promoters.

649
00:38:45.238 --> 00:38:47.858
When SMARCB1 is lost,

650
00:38:48.898 --> 00:38:52.238
you lose enhancers or decommissioned, and NRD complex removes

651
00:38:52.258 --> 00:38:56.198
predominantly to promoters, where it is antagonized by FIP.

652
00:38:56.838 --> 00:39:00.618
So whilst loss of SwitchNIF would normally lead to a shutdown of

653
00:39:00.658 --> 00:39:02.688
transcription, this is rescued by

654
00:39:03.618 --> 00:39:07.158
FIP's presence. And so when you target FIP, you now get the

655
00:39:07.218 --> 00:39:09.318
transcriptional collapse that would result.

656
00:39:10.718 --> 00:39:14.238
So I've talked about... I just mentioned that FIP, but we get

657
00:39:14.918 --> 00:39:18.558
interested then in therapeutic targeting of FIP.

