743
00:44:21.010 --> 00:44:24.450
Success in life has nothing to do with what you gain or accomplish for yourself,

744
00:44:24.510 --> 00:44:28.330
it's what you do for others. And my last takeaway point,

745
00:44:28.670 --> 00:44:31.080
I was going to say for mentors, but I think it's for everybody.

746
00:44:31.810 --> 00:44:33.710
Giving feedback is a gift.

747
00:44:34.510 --> 00:44:38.050
It helps people learn and grow. It's also a

748
00:44:38.070 --> 00:44:41.820
responsibility. And when you do it, and you engage people, and you're

749
00:44:41.870 --> 00:44:45.470
truly thinking about how it will help them, it's a

750
00:44:45.510 --> 00:44:48.490
joy to do, because then that's the way that people learn.

751
00:44:48.520 --> 00:44:52.320
It's how I learned when people gave me critical feedback in my

752
00:44:52.350 --> 00:44:56.130
career. And if I leave people with one point, this would be the

753
00:44:56.170 --> 00:44:59.530
point. So thank you to everyone who was involved.

