775
00:46:07.590 --> 00:46:11.510
So coming back to graduate training, my own son is a third-year PhD student

776
00:46:11.550 --> 00:46:14.650
in cancer biology at WashU, so I think deeply about this.

777
00:46:15.430 --> 00:46:19.390
What I say is follow what you love. Do what you love.

778
00:46:19.420 --> 00:46:23.090
It's too hard to predict the future as to what's going to be there, what's not.

779
00:46:23.130 --> 00:46:26.510
We just heard from Tony Letai. I had the privilege of hearing from him four

